The paper deals with lower bounds on randomized query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of Kolmogorov complexity, and data structures (cs.DS) in the form of block sensitivity. The paper also discusses separations between different adversary methods, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
